				<task id="task_icn_wjc_jtb"><title>Configuring log collection improvement</title><shortdesc>To configure log collection improvement in the MME, follow these        instructions.</shortdesc><prolog><author>PEIPEI SHANG</author></prolog><taskbody><context><ol><li><ph>Configure log collection improvement (WOC).</ph><info><codeph>ZWOC:2,2471,&lt;parameter                        value&gt;;</codeph><table frame="all"><title>Values of PRFILE parameter 002:2471                            IMPR_LOG_COLLECTION</title><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/><colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="3.08*"/><thead><row><entry>                                        <p>Value</p>                                    </entry><entry>                                        <p>Purpose</p>                                    </entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>                                        <p>FF</p>                                    </entry><entry>                                        <p>MME supports refined logging capabilities                                            for configured class group.</p>                                    </entry></row><row><entry>                                        <p>0</p>                                    </entry><entry>                                        <p>Default. MME does not support refined                                            logging capabilities for configured class group.</p>                                    </entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></info></li><li><ph>Fetch the <filepath>LNX924NX.INI</filepath> and                        <filepath>LNX934NX.INI</filepath> files from the                        <filepath>ASWDIR/FNSINI</filepath> directory.</ph></li><li><ph>Define the log CPU threshold.</ph><info>                    <p>The threshold can be defined to disable the log collection                        feature automatically in the LNX924NX.INI and LNX934NX.INI files.</p>                    <table frame="all"><title>CLI command for log CPU threshold</title><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/><colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.0*"/><thead><row><entry>                                        <p>CLI command</p>                                    </entry><entry>                                        <p>Usage</p>                                    </entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>                                        <p>LOG_CPU_THRESHOLD</p>                                    </entry><entry>                                        <p>This command defines the threshold to                                            disable the log collection feature automatically.</p>                                    </entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table>                </info></li><li><ph>Update the configured XML configuration files.</ph><info>                    <p>This command is used to read the values from the local JSON file and update                        the log levels of the corresponding classes.</p>                    <table frame="all"><title>CLI command for XML configuration file update</title><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/><colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.0*"/><thead><row><entry>                                        <p>CLI command</p>                                    </entry><entry>                                        <p>Usage</p>                                    </entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>                                        <p>loggerimpr read</p>                                    </entry><entry>                                        <p>Load the configuration data for logger</p>                                    </entry></row><row><entry>                                        <p>loggerimpr on</p>                                    </entry><entry>                                        <p>Reactivate the log collection improvement feature for a                                            CPPU or MMDU unit which has reached the configured                                            threshold and been disabled.</p>                                        <p>The feature is disabled automatically if the CPPU or MMDU                                            unit reaches the threshold again.</p>                                    </entry></row><row><entry>                                        <p>loggerimpr isactive</p>                                    </entry><entry>                                        <p>Show whether the log collection improvement feature is                                            enabled or disabled.</p>                                    </entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table>                    <p>For further instructions, see <cite>Modifying .INI files                        </cite>in <cite>Integrating Flexi NS - MME</cite>.</p>                </info></li></ol></context></taskbody></task>